St. John ſaith,1 Joh. 3.23. 
               This is his Commandment, that we ſhould believe on the Name of his Son Jeſus Chriſt, and love one another, as he gave us Commandment. And thus, Obedience to the great Commands of Chriſt, (whether only revealed by him, or alſo written in our Hearts) is a neceſſary part of our Religion, as well as the Belief of his Great Truths. To love the Lord our God with all our heart — and our Neighbour as our ſelves. For Chriſt is the Author of Eternal Salvation to thoſe only that obey him;

                  Mat. 22.37.39. Hebr. 5.9. 2 Tim. 1.13. and we are to hold faſt the form of ſound words in Faith and Love which is in Chriſt Jeſus.
